{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"wake-inn-parse","description":"## Reproduction Steps\n\n1. Two tickets A, B bound to Jira, with a `blocks`/`relates_to`/`depends_on` link present BOTH locally and as a Jira issuelink.\n2. Remove the link locally: `rebar unlink A B`.\n3. Run a reconcile pass (or wait for the cron).\n\n**Expected:** the Jira issuelink is removed to match local; the unlink sticks.\n**Actual:** the local unlink is silently reverted every reconcile pass — the dependency re-appears.\n\n## Root Cause\n\nSame class as the parent-detach churn (drum-ruler-suit), realized via an ADD-only design rather than a truthy-guard:\n- **Outbound** `_diff_links` is explicitly ADD-only (`outbound_differ.py:1002-1059`, docstring 'No REMOVE mutations (additive-only)'). It iterates only local `deps`; there is no 'in Jira but not local -> remove' pass. A local unlink emits nothing -> the Jira issuelink persists.\n- **Inbound** `_diff_links_inbound` is also ADD-only (`inbound_differ.py:440-514`, 'No REMOVE mutations'). On the next pass it sees the still-present Jira link with no matching local dep and emits an inbound ADD -> re-creates the dep locally.\n- **Applier**: `batch_dispatch.update_one` only calls `client.set_relationship` (add); there is NO remove/delete-link path (`batch_dispatch.py:554-595`), and the acli client has no delete-link method (only `delete_issue`). So even an emitted clear could not currently be applied.\n- Same-pass suppression only cancels inbound link-ADD echoes of outbound link-ADDs (`inbound_differ.py:743-754`); it does not help removals.\n\nNet: whichever side still holds the link re-adds it; a link removal can never converge. Bug 3f04 (`f57cdcd2`) fixed link ADD sync in both directions but left removal unhandled.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] A new acli client method removes a Jira issuelink (e.g. delete_relationship / remove_link), with a unit test.\n- [ ] Outbound `_diff_links` emits a REMOVE mutation when a link present in Jira is absent locally (symmetric with `_diff_labels`), gated like the label-remove intent gate to avoid clobbering links rebar never observed.\n- [ ] Inbound `_diff_links_inbound` emits a REMOVE when a link present locally is absent in Jira (the dual), so a Jira-side unlink mirrors to local.\n- [ ] `batch_dispatch.update_one` routes a link REMOVE through the new acli remove path, guarding HTTP errors non-fatally.\n- [ ] Same-pass suppression covers link REMOVE echoes (extend the link_add_keys mechanism to removals) so the two directions don't fight.\n- [ ] Regression tests (RED->GREEN) modeled on test_parent_detach_sync.py: local-unlink emits an outbound remove and is not re-added inbound; a never-linked pair emits nothing (no churn).","id":"908c-0f55-4a3b-4ae0","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"Issue-link/dep REMOVAL churn: same asymmetric-clear pattern as parent-detach (both differs ADD-only)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782533575790109001,"uuid":"56a39485-66f8-4733-ba19-02554c3dd914"}